Description: vendor/.env — remove hardcoded OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH
 Audit B3 (docs/260418-dual-sensitivity-analysis.md §5.2) flags
 `vendor/obsidian-wiki/.env` line 9 as pointing at the knlg-repo root
 rather than a zone-scoped vault path. In dual-zone mode this mis-routes
 any skill that falls back to reading vendor/.env when pre-loaded env
 vars are absent.
 .
 Audit reco was option A (delete vendor/.env entirely). That was rejected
 here in favour of option B (keep the file but blank the offending
 value) because :
 .
   1. `.env` is gitignored by the vendor repo (`git ls-files` reports it
      absent from HEAD and from the index). A pure delete patch can only
      be expressed against an untracked working-tree file, which breaks
      `git apply --index` used by the jalon-6 apply engine.
   2. Blanking the value (`OBSIDIAN_VAULT_PATH=`) preserves the
      fallback mechanism for skills that expect the file to exist, while
      preventing mis-routing (an empty value causes a fail-fast in the
      skill instead of silently hitting the wrong directory).
   3. B4 is subsumed : once the value is blank, the "wrong directory"
      regression disappears without a separate patch.
 .
 Deviation documented in patches/README.md §"B3 deviation".
